HEADWORD: Pneumatocyst
<hw>Pneu*mat"o*cyst</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Pneumato-</ets> + <ets>cyst</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A cyst or sac of a siphonophore, containing air, and serving as a
float, as in Physalia.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

